body:
Hey @lluzak !

A userland solution would be to create a custom cache that bails the first `read`/`write` : 

```ts
const cache = createInfiniteHitsSessionStorageCache();

const ssrSafeCache: typeof cache & {
  firstReadDone: boolean;
  firstWriteDone: boolean;
} = {
  firstReadDone: false,
  firstWriteDone: false,
  read({ state }) {
    if (!this.firstReadDone) {
      this.firstReadDone = true;
      return null;
    }
    return cache.read({ state });
  },
  write({ state, hits }) {
    if (!this.firstWriteDone) {
      this.firstWriteDone = true;
      return;
    }
    cache.write({ state, hits });
  },
};
```

You can see it in action there : https://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/confident-moon-vhm9rq?file=%2Fpages%2Findex.tsx%3A24%2C1-46%2C3

Unfortunately this will lead to a small layout shift, but let me know if it works for you !

I'll look if it's possible to handle it directly in the lib, if not we can document or package this SSR-safe cache.
